<p>Geographic variations across Indiana show that southern regions of the state generally receive slightly higher solar irradiance than northern areas, but the difference is minimal enough that solar panels remain cost-effective throughout the entire state. Cities like Evansville, Indianapolis, and Fort Wayne all demonstrate strong solar production potential, with south-facing roof installations typically achieving the highest energy yields. Modern solar panels perform well even in Indiana's variable weather conditions, generating electricity during cloudy days and maintaining efficiency in cold winter temperatures.</p>

