    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">How much do solar panels cost in Indiana?</h3>
    <p>Solar panel costs in Indiana typically range from \$2.30 to \$2.80 per watt before incentives, with complete residential systems averaging \$12,000 to \$34,000 depending on size. After applying the 30% federal tax credit, homeowners can expect to pay between \$8,400 and \$23,800 for turnkey solar installations. The final cost depends on factors including system size, equipment quality, roof complexity, and local installation rates. Most Indiana homeowners see payback periods of 8-12 years based on current electricity rates and solar production levels.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What SEER rating is recommended for Indiana?</h3>
    <p>For Indiana's climate, HVAC systems with SEER ratings of 16-18 provide the optimal balance of efficiency and cost-effectiveness. While the federal minimum SEER requirement is 14, higher efficiency units deliver better performance during Indiana's hot, humid summers. Heat pumps with SEER ratings above 16 qualify for federal tax credits, while units with 18+ SEER ratings provide maximum energy savings. For homeowners planning long-term ownership, investing in 18-20 SEER equipment typically provides the best return on investment through reduced operating costs.</p>
  </div>
  
