    <p>Solar panels are designed to withstand Indiana's variable weather conditions and typically last 25-30 years with minimal performance degradation. Most manufacturers provide 20-25 year warranties guaranteeing at least 80% of original production capacity. Indiana's climate, including snow, hail, and temperature variations, poses no significant threat to quality solar installations when properly designed and installed. Regular maintenance, including occasional cleaning and annual inspections, helps ensure optimal performance throughout the system's lifespan.</p>
  </div>
  
