    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What permits are required for solar installation in Indiana?</h3>
    <p>Solar installations in Indiana typically require building permits from local authorities and electrical permits for grid interconnection. Most residential installations under 25kW follow standardized permitting processes that solar contractors handle on behalf of homeowners. Required documentation includes system design plans, equipment specifications, structural calculations, and electrical diagrams. Duke Energy requires interconnection applications for grid-tied systems, which include utility-grade production meters and safety disconnect switches. Professional solar installers manage all permitting requirements, ensuring compliance with local building codes and utility standards.</p>
